about worklife worklife office stanford university worklife office supporting full engagement in work and life search web pages submit about worklife navigating work and life on site child care elder care education and resources child care resources about worklife introduction the worklife office was established in 1989 through the tireless efforts of dorthea almond and phylis craig initially child and family resources worklife programs and services have expanded to meet the diverse needs of the ever changing stanford community a worklife trailblazer stanford was the first university to be named in the working mothers 100 best places to work and is a founding member of the college and university work family association stanford has also been recognized for its adoption assistance program by concieve magazine and the dave thomas foundation quicklinks child care subsidy grant financial assistance programs appointment request child care information request sign up for parent net stanford parents only contact worklife sacc update adoption events brown bags caregivers group events calendar summer activities fair documents child care packet child care eligibility lactation spaces child care application home mission of worklife the mission of the worklife office is to support the university's academic mission through direct services and collaborative partnerships that assist faculty staff and students in reaching a comfortable balance in their work study personal and family lives alliance for work life progress awlp stanford benefits college and university worfk family association cuwfa history of worklife human resources collaboration programs the worklife office delivers programs and services in seven different areas from birth to end of life in the form of education and training direct services financial assistance and resource and referral active aging living well child care resources elder care and caregiver resources financial assistance programs navigating work and 